# NirmiqLearn OS — Windsurf Rules

## Project
Local-first AI learning OS built with Next.js 16 + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS 4.
Students build with AI but must genuinely understand their projects.

## Session Start
1. Read docs/CONTEXT.md.
2. Read docs/GRAPHIFY_MAP.md to locate relevant files without scanning the repo.
3. Read only the task-specific doc: TRD (technical), UI_UX (UI), DEBUGGING (bugs), PRD (product).

## Coding Rules
- TypeScript strict mode. No `any`.
- Small components. Max ~200 lines per file.
- Zod validation at all system boundaries.
- Service result type: `{ ok: true; data: T } | { ok: false; error: string; code?: string }`.
- Drizzle ORM for all DB access. No raw SQL unless necessary.
- Zustand for UI state only — never for persistent data.

## UI Constraints
- Theme: dark, academic, premium. Near-black background, cyan accent.
- Component library: shadcn/ui.
- Layout: left sidebar + topbar + main content + optional right panel.
- Every page must answer: "What do I do next?"

